Pop the #stock pot{} into a large #saucepan{} and grate in the @lemon{½}(zested).

Pour the boiling @water{300%ml} into the pan and pop on medium-high heat, stir to dissolve the @vegetable stock powder{½}.

Stir in the @couscous{150%g}, cover with a #lid{}, remove from the heat and leave for ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{200}.

Pop the @easy garlic{½}, @king prawns{120}, @sugar snap peas{150%g}, cherry plum tomatoes, the juice from the lemon and the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} into a large #bowl{}.

Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}, toss to combine and set aside.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{30%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Tip in the entire contents of the bowl with the prawns in and stir-fry until the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Fluff up the couscous.

Gently mix together the prawn medley and the couscous, then sprinkle over the @dukkah mix{1%packet} and half the parsley and toss to combine.

Serve the dukkah prawn jumble with a drizzle of @sweet chilli sauce{32%ml} and a sprinkling of the remaining parsley. Enjoy!